oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Greer and Carmichael Store construction
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the Greer and Carmichael Store at 604 Grove Street during construction. Men are standing on each level of the construction site. Large piles of bricks are on the ground. The store was located across from the county courthouse and the Carmichael Inn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stores & shops; Construction; Bricks
